-- Taiwan Stocks: Everlight Electronics, Formosa Epitaxy, Largan
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-04-18T05:47:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/taiwan-stocks-catcher-technology-epistar-largan-precision.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 0.3 percent to 7,605.  Everlight Electronics Co. (2393)  (2393 TT) increased 2.7 percent
to NT$63.90.  Formosa Epitaxy Inc. (3061)  (3061 TT) climbed 2.2 percent
to NT$25.85. Demand for light-emitting diodes surged after
Taiwan raised electricity prices for the first time in more than
three years, the Economic Daily News reported, without saying
where it got the information.  Largan Precision Co. (3008)  (3008 TT) advanced 2 percent to
NT$560. The lens company was raised to neutral from sell at UBS
AG, with a price target of NT$560. This means investors should
hold the same proportion of the stock that is represented in
benchmark indexes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
